<span id="freeTextContainer15859309265670201432">If you&apos;re into stuff like this, <a href='https://manuelaantao.blogspot.com/1980/10/magic-undercover-amber-series-by-roger.html' rel='nofollow noopener'>you can read the full review.</a><br/><br/><br/>Magic Undercover: &quot;The Amber Series&quot; by Roger Zelazny<br/><br/><br/><br/>(Original Review, 1980)<br/><br/><br/>1 - The Amber series has had a great impact on the field they say.<br/><br/>I have serious doubts about whether that is true. I will leave someone else to develop those arguments. However, in any case Farmer&apos;s WORLD OF TIERS series does NOT support this contention. The AMBER series is derived from the WORLD OF TIERS series. The primary difference is that TIERS uses a tec</span>
  <span id="freeText15859309265670201432" style="display:none">If you're into stuff like this, <a href="https://manuelaantao.blogspot.com/1980/10/magic-undercover-amber-series-by-roger.html" rel="nofollow noopener">you can read the full review.</a><br /><br /><br />Magic Undercover: "The Amber Series" by Roger Zelazny<br /><br /><br /><br />(Original Review, 1980)<br /><br /><br />1 - The Amber series has had a great impact on the field they say.<br /><br />I have serious doubts about whether that is true. I will leave someone else to develop those arguments. However, in any case Farmer's WORLD OF TIERS series does NOT support this contention. The AMBER series is derived from the WORLD OF TIERS series. The primary difference is that TIERS uses a technological background for the basic structure of the universe and AMBER uses a magical background.</span>
