  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/880556163" />
    <a title="Kimberley doruyter" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23952659-kimberley-doruyter"><img alt="Kimberley doruyter" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1547842800p2/23952659.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/880556163?book_show_action=true">Mar 13, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kimberley doruyter" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kimberley doruyter" href="/user/show/23952659-kimberley-doruyter">Kimberley doruyter</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer880556163" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9491417358402612633">as a whole this series is the most fantastical fantasy world i have as yet come across.<br/>i did like the first five a little better then the last five.<br/>i loved the character of corwin, he was wonderful and unlike most of the rest of his family he seemed to have more good then bad.<br/>his son has much the as history.<br/>i recommend this book to all how have read fantasy before, it is something different from the mainstream of the genre.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


